    "description": "Wire-name -> category lookup for the Qwashed HNDL classifier. Categories are: classical (HNDL-vulnerable), hybrid_pq (classical || PQ co-installed), pq_only (post-quantum primitive only), unknown (treated as worst-case classical for fail-closed scoring). When updating: keep entries lowercase except where the protocol RFC or IANA registry uses a specific case (e.g. cipher suite identifiers are upper snake case). Unknown entries are NOT listed; the classifier treats anything missing from this table as 'unknown'."
